title: NASA astrophysics, commercial satellites launch on SpaceX rideshare mission
summary: A SpaceX Falcon 9 launched multiple commercial and NASA astrophysics satellites, including payloads from companies like Iceye, Capella Space, and Umbra, as well as three NASA missions. The launch was part of SpaceX's rideshare program.

entities.name: ICEYE
entities.involvement: mentioned as one of the companies with satellites on the launch

entities.name: NASA
entities.involvement: funded and developed astrophysics missions on the launch
